			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Jane Churchon</span></strong> lives in Sacramento, California, where she works as a nursing supervisor. It is her conviction that she was meant to be independently wealthy, and she remains optimistic that one can win the lottery without actually purchasing a ticket. Her work has appeared in <em>Berkeley Fiction Review</em>, <em>American River Review</em>, and the anthology <em>A Cup of Comfort for Nurses</em> (Adams Media Corporation).</p><a href="/contributors/jane-churchon" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
